[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Hawzien"]}," (also spelt ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hawzen"]},") is a town in the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Gheralta"]}," area of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tigray"]]}," region of northern ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Ethiopia"]]},". It is frequently used as a base for exploring the many rock-hewn churches of north-eastern Tigray.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nThe easiest access is to turn off Highway 1 at Sinkata (as known as Freweyni), from where it is 23 km on a good gravel road. Drive time from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mekele"]]}," via Sinkata is 2 hours 15 min. An alternative when coming from Mekele, which will take 15 minutes longer, is to turn off Highway 1 at Wukro and drive via Degum and Megab. There are also rougher roads that come in from the west, turning off the road from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Adwa"]]}," south to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abi Addi"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":["Rock-hewn churches"]},". There are over 100 of them in the Hawzien–Wukro–Sinkata area, some of them rarely visited by outsiders."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Gheralta Lodge"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.gheraltalodgetigrai.com\/"],["email=info@gheraltalodgetigrai.com"],["address="],["lat=13.9703"],["long=39.4235"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["price=450–750 birr per person (seasonal variation)"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Connect"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value